('professor', 'Denying the antecedent is ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. always valid", "B. formally invalid", "C. the same as modus ponens", "D. a strong analogy"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '否定前件為無效推論。'),
('professor', 'A deductively valid argument can still be ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. unsound if premises are false", "B. always sound", "C. inductive", "D. self-refuting always"]'::jsonb, 'A', 0, '有效論證若前提假仍可 unsound。'),
('professor', 'An ad hoc rescue revises a theory ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. before testing", "B. only to protect it from falsification", "C. using statistics only", "D. through translation"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '特設性防衛為免於被否證而補救。'),
('professor', 'Straw man fallacy involves ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. using analogies", "B. misrepresenting an opponent''s view", "C. appealing to pity", "D. equivocation only"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '稻草人謬誤扭曲對方論點。'),
('professor', 'Equivocation shifts ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. tenses", "B. the meaning of a key term", "C. font size", "D. sample size"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '歧義謬誤偷換關鍵詞義。'),
('professor', 'Post hoc ergo propter hoc mistakes ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. correlation for authentication", "B. sequence for causation", "C. cause for correlation", "D. definition for example"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '後此謬誤把先後當因果。'),
('professor', 'Begging the question ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. asks politely", "B. assumes the conclusion in premises", "C. uses only empirical data", "D. avoids pronouns"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '循環論證把結論藏於前提。'),
('professor', 'The word ''otiose'' most nearly means ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. meticulous", "B. superfluous", "C. rapid", "D. fragrant"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'otiose 意為多餘、無用。'),
('professor', 'The word ''perspicacious'' suggests ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. sloppy thinking", "B. keen insight", "C. physical strength", "D. anger"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'perspicacious 表示敏銳洞察。'),
('professor', 'The word ''recalcitrant'' fits ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. a willing volunteer", "B. a stubborn resistor", "C. a transparent liquid", "D. a cheap fabric"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'recalcitrant 形容頑抗不服。'),
('professor', 'The word ''sycophant'' denotes ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. a wise teacher", "B. a servile flatterer", "C. a neutral judge", "D. a brave pioneer"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'sycophant 為阿諛奉承者。'),
('professor', 'The word ''laconic'' describes speech that is ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. lengthy", "B. brief", "C. loud", "D. archaic"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'laconic 表示簡潔寡言。'),
('professor', 'The idiom ''to pull someone''s leg'' means ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. to help them walk", "B. to tease or joke", "C. to betray them", "D. to lend money"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '英式幽默表示開玩笑、捉弄。'),
('professor', 'The idiom ''bury the hatchet'' means ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. hide tools", "B. make peace", "C. start a fight", "D. plant trees"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '言歸於好、止息爭端。'),
('professor', 'The idiom ''let sleeping dogs lie'' advises ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. wake pets", "B. avoid stirring up trouble", "C. train animals", "D. sleep more"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '勿挑起不必要的麻煩。'),
('professor', 'The idiom ''the ball is in your court'' means ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. play tennis", "B. it''s your turn to act", "C. you lost", "D. the game ended"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '輪到你採取行動。'),
('professor', 'The idiom ''cut corners'' suggests ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. meticulous work", "B. doing something hastily or improperly", "C. taking a shortcut road only", "D. building squares"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '偷工減料、走捷徑敷衍。'),
('professor', 'An oxymoron pairs ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. synonyms", "B. contradictory terms", "C. foreign words", "D. rhyming words"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '矛盾修辭並置相反概念。'),
('professor', 'Epistemic modality expresses ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. obligation about the past", "B. speaker''s degree of commitment to truth", "C. physical ability only", "D. future tense only"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '認識情態表說話者對命題真假的確信度。'),
('professor', 'Deictic expressions depend on ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. Latin roots", "B. utterance context", "C. metrical stress", "D. silent letters"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '指示詞依賴語境座標。'),
('professor', 'A minimal pair in phonology demonstrates ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. free variation", "B. phonemic contrast", "C. allophony only", "D. tone sandhi"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '最小對立組顯示音位對立。'),
('professor', 'Complementary distribution typically indicates ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. phonemes", "B. allophones of one phoneme", "C. minimal pairs", "D. word stress"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '互補分布多為同一音位之變體。'),
('professor', 'The passive voice is sometimes preferred in scientific writing to ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. increase wordiness", "B. foreground the process or result", "C. avoid verbs", "D. hide subject always"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '被動可突出過程或結果。'),
('professor', 'The rhetorical question primarily functions to ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. request information only", "B. prompt reflection rather than an answer", "C. change tense", "D. translate literally"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '反問用於引發思考而非真問。'),
('professor', 'Pathos appeals to ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. logic", "B. credibility", "C. emotion", "D. grammar"]'::jsonb, 'C', 2, '悲情訴諸情感 pathos。'),
('professor', 'Logos appeals to ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. emotion", "B. character", "C. reasoning and evidence", "D. rhythm"]'::jsonb, 'C', 2, '理性訴諸論證 logos。'),
('professor', 'Ethos appeals to ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. statistics only", "B. speaker credibility", "C. musicality", "D. imagery only"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '人格訴諸可信度 ethos。'),
('professor', 'Ambiguity of scope may confuse whether ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. a verb is transitive", "B. negation applies to one clause or another", "C. nouns are plural", "D. letters are silent"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '範域歧義影響否定範圍。'),
('professor', 'Vagueness differs from ambiguity because vagueness ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. has two precise senses", "B. involves borderline cases", "C. is always grammatical", "D. requires synonyms"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '模糊涉及界線案例而非雙義。'),
('professor', 'Performative utterances ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. cannot be spoken", "B. do something by being said", "C. only describe weather", "D. lack verbs"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '施為句以說出即完成行為。'),
('professor', 'Implicature (Gricean) relies on ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. literal grammar only", "B. conversational cooperation and context", "C. spelling rules", "D. IPA charts"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '含意依合作原則與語境推導。'),
('professor', 'A malapropism is ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. a deliberate pun", "B. an amusing word substitution error", "C. a silent letter", "D. a dialect map"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '誤用近似音詞造成滑稽效果。'),
('professor', 'Proprioceptive imagery appeals to ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. sight", "B. internal bodily sensation", "C. hearing", "D. taste only"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '本體感覺意象描寫身體內部感覺。'),
('professor', 'Synesthesia in literature ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. avoids metaphor", "B. crosses sensory domains", "C. uses only facts", "D. removes adjectives"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '通感跨感官域。'),
('professor', 'The hedging phrase ''I might be wrong, but...'' serves to ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. assert certainty", "B. soften the claim", "C. change topic", "D. quote sources"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '模糊限制語弱化斷言。'),
('professor', 'Parallelism in prose primarily enhances ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. confusion", "B. rhythm and clarity", "C. spelling", "D. font choice"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '排比增節奏與清晰度。'),
('professor', 'Antimetabole repeats words in ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. random order", "B. reverse order", "C. alphabetical order", "D. silent letters"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '逆序重複為 antimetabole。'),
('professor', 'The pathetic fallacy attributes human emotion to ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. numbers", "B. nature or objects", "C. verbs only", "D. footnotes"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '感情誤置賦予自然或物情感。'),
('professor', 'An enthymeme in rhetoric is ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. a long poem", "B. a syllogism with an unstated premise", "C. a type of irony", "D. a grammar rule"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '省略三段論省略前提。'),
('professor', 'The distinction between ''fewer'' and ''less'' is prescriptively about ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. formality", "B. count vs mass nouns", "C. British vs American", "D. past vs present"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '規範上 fewer 配可數、less 配不可數。'),
('professor', 'In philosophy of language, ''extension'' of a term is ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. its intension", "B. the set of things it denotes", "C. its etymology", "D. its pronunciation"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '外延為詞所指對象集合。'),
('professor', 'The intension of a word includes ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. only pronunciation", "B. associative or definitional properties", "C. only spelling", "D. rhyme scheme"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '內涵為定義性質與屬性。'),
('professor', 'If P implies Q, then ''not Q'' implies ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. P", "B. not P", "C. Q", "D. P and Q"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '拒取式：非 Q 則非 P（假設原為 P→Q）。'),
('professor', 'A contingent truth is one that ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. must be true in all worlds", "B. could have been otherwise", "C. is self-contradictory", "D. only concerns math"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '偶然真理可以不是如此。'),
('professor', 'Analytic statements are often characterized as ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. empirical", "B. true by virtue of meaning", "C. always false", "D. poetic"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '分析句依意義為真。'),
('professor', 'Synthetic statements ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. are true by definition only", "B. combine concepts not contained in the subject", "C. cannot be false", "D. lack predicates"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '綜合句把主詞所無之概念連結起來。'),
('professor', 'The fallacy of composition assumes ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. parts equal whole properties", "B. what is true of parts is true of the whole", "C. correlation implies causation", "D. experts are wrong"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '合成謬誤以部分性質推整體。'),
('professor', 'The fallacy of division assumes ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. the whole''s property belongs to every part", "B. correlation is causation", "C. samples are random", "D. definitions shift"]'::jsonb, 'A', 0, '分割謬誤以整體屬性推每一部分。'),
('professor', 'A virtue of a clear operational definition is that it ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. avoids all measurement", "B. makes variables observable and testable", "C. removes ethics", "D. eliminates theory"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '操作型定義使變項可觀測檢驗。'),
('professor', 'In academic hedging, the verb suggests is weaker than ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. might", "B. proves", "C. could", "D. may"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'suggests 比 proves 語氣弱。'),
('elementary', 'My mother and father ___ teachers.', '["A. am", "B. is", "C. are", "D. be"]'::jsonb, 'C', 2, '複數主詞 parents 用 are。'),
('elementary', 'My grandfather ___ reading every morning.', '["A. am", "B. is", "C. are", "D. be"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '第三人稱單數用 is。'),
('elementary', '___ there any milk left (choose the best option)?', '["A. Is", "B. Are", "C. Am", "D. Do"]'::jsonb, 'A', 0, '不可數 milk 與 there be 搭配用 Is there。'),
('elementary', '___ those your stickers (choose the best option)?', '["A. Is", "B. Are", "C. Am", "D. Was"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'those 複數用 Are。'),
('elementary', 'I ___ not hungry. (choose the best option).', '["A. am", "B. is", "C. are", "D. be"]'::jsonb, 'A', 0, 'I 配 am。'),
('elementary', 'We ___ from Canada. (choose the best option).', '["A. am", "B. is", "C. are", "D. be"]'::jsonb, 'C', 2, 'We 複數用 are。'),
('elementary', '___ does the shop open (choose the best option)?', '["A. When", "B. Who", "C. Whose", "D. Which"]'::jsonb, 'A', 0, '問時間用 When。'),
('elementary', '___ bag are you carrying (choose the best option)?', '["A. Who", "B. Which", "C. Whose", "D. Where"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '問哪一個／款式用 Which。'),
('elementary', 'Every weekend she ___ her grandma. (choose the best option).', '["A. visit", "B. visits", "C. visiting", "D. visited"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '習慣動作 she + visit + s。'),
('elementary', 'They ___ football right now.', '["A. play", "B. plays", "C. are playing", "D. played"]'::jsonb, 'C', 2, 'now 表現在進行。'),
('elementary', 'Look! It ___ . (choose the best option).', '["A. rain", "B. rains", "C. is raining", "D. rained"]'::jsonb, 'C', 2, 'Look 提示正在發生。'),
('elementary', 'I ___ never ___ sushi. (choose the best option).', '["A. have / eat", "B. have / eaten", "C. has / eaten", "D. had / eat"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '現在完成式 have eaten。'),
('elementary', 'She ___ to Tokyo twice. (choose the best option).', '["A. go", "B. goes", "C. has gone", "D. went"]'::jsonb, 'C', 2, '經驗次數用現在完成式。'),
('elementary', 'Before bed I always ___ my teeth. (choose the best option).', '["A. brush", "B. brushes", "C. brushing", "D. brushed"]'::jsonb, 'A', 0, 'I + always + 現在式 brush。'),
('elementary', 'Can we ___ outside (choose the best option)?', '["A. plays", "B. play", "C. playing", "D. played"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'can 後接原形。'),
('elementary', 'She ___ play the piano when she was six. (choose the best option).', '["A. can", "B. could", "C. may", "D. must"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '過去能力用 could。'),
('elementary', 'You ___ wear a helmet on this ride. (choose the best option).', '["A. should", "B. shouldn''t", "C. might", "D. could"]'::jsonb, 'A', 0, '安全規定建議 should。'),
('elementary', 'It is dark. You ___ leave alone.', '["A. should", "B. shouldn''t", "C. must", "D. might"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '危險情境建議不要.shouldn''t。'),
('elementary', 'There ___ many kinds of juice in the jug. (choose the best option).', '["A. is", "B. are", "C. be", "D. am"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'kinds 為可數複數，用 there are。'),
('elementary', 'How ___ students are in the club (choose the best option)?', '["A. much", "B. many", "C. long", "D. often"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '可數名詞數量用 How many。'),
('elementary', 'How ___ does the ticket cost (choose the best option)?', '["A. many", "B. much", "C. often", "D. far"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '價錢用 How much。'),
('elementary', 'I would like ___ water, please.', '["A. any", "B. some", "C. many", "D. few"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '肯定請求液體用 some。'),
('elementary', 'We don''t have ___ eggs. (choose the best option).', '["A. some", "B. any", "C. much", "D. many"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '否定句「任何」用 any。'),
('elementary', 'That is ___ elephant. (choose the best option).', '["A. a", "B. an", "C. the", "D. no article"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'elephant 母音開頭用 an。'),
('elementary', 'Pass me ___ salt. (choose the best option).', '["A. a", "B. an", "C. the", "D. no article"]'::jsonb, 'C', 2, '特指桌上的鹽用 the。'),
('elementary', '___ Earth goes around the Sun. (choose the best option).', '["A. A", "B. An", "C. The", "D. no article"]'::jsonb, 'C', 2, '獨一無二事物用 the。'),
('elementary', 'I''ve lost ___ pen you lent me. (choose the best option).', '["A. a", "B. an", "C. the", "D. no article"]'::jsonb, 'C', 2, '特定那支筆用 the。'),
('elementary', 'She runs ___ than her brother. (choose the best option).', '["A. fast", "B. faster", "C. fastest", "D. more fast"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '兩者比較用比較級 faster。'),
('elementary', 'This is the ___ pizza I''ve ever had. (choose the best option).', '["A. good", "B. better", "C. best", "D. more good"]'::jsonb, 'C', 2, 'ever 搭配最高級 best。'),
('elementary', 'My room is ___ than yours. (choose the best option).', '["A. big", "B. bigger", "C. biggest", "D. more big"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'than 用比較級 bigger。'),
('elementary', 'She speaks English ___ . (choose the best option).', '["A. good", "B. well", "C. better", "D. best"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '修飾動詞 speak 用副詞 well。'),
('elementary', '___ carefully, please! (choose the best option).', '["A. Listen", "B. Listen to", "C. Hear", "D. Sound"]'::jsonb, 'A', 0, '祈使「聽」用 Listen（不及物）。'),
('elementary', '___ you help me carry this (choose the best option)?', '["A. Can", "B. Should", "C. Must", "D. May"]'::jsonb, 'A', 0, '請求協助常用 Can。'),
('elementary', 'I am interested ___ science fiction.', '["A. on", "B. in", "C. at", "D. for"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'be interested in。'),
('elementary', 'Good ___! You''ll do better next time. (choose the best option).', '["A. luck", "B. luckily", "C. lucky", "D. unlucky"]'::jsonb, 'A', 0, '安慰常用 Good luck 或加油語境。'),
('elementary', 'See you ___ weekend! (choose the best option).', '["A. this", "B. at this", "C. on this", "D. the"]'::jsonb, 'A', 0, 'this weekend 固定說法。'),
('elementary', '___ happy birthday! (choose the best option).', '["A. Say", "B. Wish", "C. Tell", "D. Speak"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '祝賀生日常用 Wish。'),
('elementary', 'Turn ___ the TV; it''s too loud. (choose the best option).', '["A. on", "B. off", "C. up", "D. in"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '太吵要關掉用 turn off。'),
('elementary', '___ up early makes me tired. (choose the best option).', '["A. Wake", "B. Waking", "C. Woke", "D. Wakes"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '主詞用動名詞 Waking。'),
('elementary', 'I would like ___ pizza slice.', '["A. other", "B. another", "C. others", "D. the other"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '再一片（不定數中再一個）用 another。'),
('elementary', 'Both answers ___ wrong. (choose the best option).', '["A. is", "B. are", "C. am", "D. was"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'Both + 複數名詞用 are。'),
('elementary', 'Neither answer ___ correct. (choose the best option).', '["A. are", "B. is", "C. were", "D. be"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'Neither + 單數名詞視為單數 is。'),
('elementary', 'Put your toys ___ the box. (choose the best option).', '["A. at", "B. on", "C. in", "D. to"]'::jsonb, 'C', 2, '放入盒子內部用 in。'),
('elementary', 'The poster is ___ the wall. (choose the best option).', '["A. in", "B. on", "C. at", "D. over"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '貼在牆面上用 on。'),
('elementary', 'We will meet ___ noon.', '["A. on", "B. in", "C. at", "D. by"]'::jsonb, 'C', 2, '時刻 at noon。'),
('elementary', '___ spring, flowers bloom. (choose the best option).', '["A. On", "B. At", "C. In", "D. By"]'::jsonb, 'C', 2, '季節用 in。'),
('elementary', 'We''re traveling ___ plane. (choose the best option).', '["A. by", "B. on", "C. with", "D. in"]'::jsonb, 'A', 0, '交通工具 by plane。'),
('elementary', 'I am afraid ___ spiders.', '["A. for", "B. of", "C. about", "D. with"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'be afraid of。'),
('elementary', 'Could you please speak ___ slowly?', '["A. more", "B. many", "C. much", "D. most"]'::jsonb, 'A', 0, '請對方「再慢一點」用 more slowly。'),
('elementary', 'This puzzle is easy ___ me. (choose the best option).', '["A. for", "B. to", "C. with", "D. of"]'::jsonb, 'A', 0, '對某人而言簡單用 for。'),
('elementary', 'What is the opposite of ''cheap''?', '["A. small", "B. expensive", "C. short", "D. cold"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'cheap 的反義常用 expensive。'),
('elementary', 'Which month comes ___ October (choose the best option)?', '["A. before", "B. after", "C. between", "D. during"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '十一月接在十月之後。'),
('elementary', 'A rectangle has ___ sides. (choose the best option).', '["A. three", "B. four", "C. five", "D. six"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '長方形四邊。'),
('elementary', 'Water freezes at ___ Celsius. (choose the best option).', '["A. 0", "B. 32", "C. 100", "D. 50"]'::jsonb, 'A', 0, '水的冰點攝氏 0 度。'),
('elementary', 'Which animal lives in water and jumps (choose the best option)?', '["A. lion", "B. frog", "C. cow", "D. eagle"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '青蛙典型在水邊／水中活動並跳躍。'),
('elementary', 'You cut vegetables with a ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. ball", "B. knife", "C. hat", "D. pillow"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '用刀切菜。'),
('elementary', 'We listen to music with our ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. eyes", "B. ears", "C. nose", "D. hands"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '耳朵聽音樂。'),
('elementary', 'What do you use to tell time (choose the best option)?', '["A. a map", "B. a clock", "C. a spoon", "D. a pillow"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '時鐘看時間。'),
('elementary', 'If you are hungry, you want ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. sleep", "B. food", "C. ice", "D. darkness"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '餓了想吃東西。'),
('elementary', 'This juice tastes ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. sweetly", "B. sweet", "C. sweetness", "D. sweeter"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '感官動詞 taste 後接形容詞 sweet。'),
