('professor', 'Truthmaker semantics ties truth to ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. only syntax trees", "B. what makes sentences true", "C. only phonetics", "D. only etymology"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '使真者語義。'),
('professor', 'Supervaluationism handles vagueness by ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. banning logic", "B. quantifying over admissible sharpenings", "C. only dictionaries", "D. only homophones"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '超評估值：可容許細化。'),
('professor', 'Type-logical approaches link syntax and semantics via ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. random mapping", "B. curry-howard style proofs", "C. only stress", "D. only orthography"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '類型邏輯／句法語義介面。'),
('professor', 'Proof-theoretic semantics privileges ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. only dictionaries", "B. inferential rules over truth conditions alone", "C. only orthography", "D. only IPA"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '證明論語義：推導規則。'),
('professor', 'Lexical semantics decomposition debates whether features are ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. always universal across languages", "B. language-particular or universal", "C. only phonetic", "D. only orthographic"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '詞彙分解：特徵是否普世。'),
('professor', 'Polysemy networks are often modeled as ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. isolated lists", "B. radial categories with motivated extensions", "C. only rhyme pairs", "D. only homonyms"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '多義網路：放射狀範疇。'),
('professor', 'Construction grammar treats ___ as basic. (choose the best option).', '["A. only morphemes", "B. form-meaning pairings at multiple sizes", "C. only syllables", "D. only phonemes"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '構式語法：多層級形義配對。'),
('professor', 'Grammaticalization typically involves ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. only borrowing", "B. semantic bleaching and category shifts", "C. only stress movement", "D. only spelling reform"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '語法化：語義淡化與範疇轉移。'),
('professor', 'Grammaticalization clines suggest change is ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. instantaneous always", "B. gradient rather than strictly abrupt", "C. only phonetic", "D. only lexical"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '斜坡／漸變。'),
('professor', 'Areal diffusion explains ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. only genetic relationships", "B. similarities via contact between languages", "C. only universal grammar", "D. only orthography"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '區域擴散：接觸相似。'),
('professor', 'Substrate influence often surfaces in ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. only genetic trees", "B. lexicon and phonology of a dominant language", "C. only tense", "D. only spelling"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '底層語影響。'),
('professor', 'Diachronic reconstruction uses ___. (choose the best option).', '["A. only modern dictionaries", "B. the comparative method among cognates", "C. only rhyme", "D. only stress"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '歷史比較法。');
